Author: cascrypto#8206
Content: Another example is where a secondary market transaction involves a broker-dealer introducing a buyer to a seller of digital asset securities through a trading platform where the trade is settled directly between the buyer and seller.  For instance, a broker-dealer that operates an alternative trading system (‚ÄúATS‚Äù) could match buyers and sellers of digital asset securities and the trades would either be settled directly between the buyer and seller, or the buyer and seller would give instructions to their respective custodians to settle the transactions.[9]  In either case, the ATS would not guarantee or otherwise have responsibility for settling the trades and would not at any time exercise any level of control over the digital asset securities being sold or the cash being used to make the purchase (e.g., the ATS would not place a temporary hold on the seller‚Äôs wallet or on the buyer‚Äôs cash to ensure the transaction is completed).
